'''Joe Dempsie''' (born 22 June 1987) is a British actor. He is best known for playing [[wikipedia:Chris Miles|Chris Miles]] in the drama series ''[[wikipedia:Skins (TV series)|Skins]]'', but has also appeared in ''[[wikipedia:Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]'', ''[[wikipedia:Doctor Who|Doctor Who]],'' ''[[wikipedia:Merlin (TV series)|Merlin]]'' and ''[[wikipedia:This is England '86|This is England '86]]''.

In ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' he plays the role of [[Gendry]]. He was confirmed in the role on 11 August 2010. He initially appeared as a guest star in the [[Season 1|first season]] and returned in this role for the [[Season 2|second season]]Â and [[Season 3|third season]]'s.

Prior to being cast as Gendry, Dempsie had auditioned for the roles of [[Jon Snow]], [[Pypar]], and [[Grenn]].&lt;ref&gt;McLean, Craig (April 15, 2013). [http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2013-04-15/meet-the-british-stars-of-game-of-thrones Meet the British stars of Game of Thrones] Radio Times.&lt;/ref&gt;

Joe Dempsie tweeted on the 17th June &quot;Still rowin'...&quot;, to explain Gendry's absence in Season 4, referring to how he was last seen rowing back to King's Landing from Dragonstone.
